    <div class="card-body">
    <h3>Lightweight Swarm Communication for Drones and Robots</h3>
    <p>ROS2/DDS multicast storms kill WiFi. MAVLink has no encryption. A single 10MB binary gives robot swarms encrypted pub/sub, NAT traversal, and tag-based discovery.</p>
    <div class="meta"><span class="date">Feb 25</span><span>Robotics</span><span class="tag">drones</span><span class="tag">swarm</span></div>
    </div>
  </a>

  <a class="blog-card" href="smart-home-without-cloud-local-device-communication.html">
